HEADWORD: Hamilton period
<hw>Ham"il*ton pe"ri*od</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧m"⟦icr⟧l*t⟦ucr⟧n
p⟦emac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*⟦ucr⟧d)</pr>. <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A subdivision of
the Devonian system of America; -- so named from
<etsep>Hamilton</etsep>, Madison Co., New York. It includes the
Marcellus, Hamilton, and Genesee epochs or groups. See the Chart of
<er>Geology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Haminoea</ent>⟦br⟧
